A man who found a travel partner after raffling his ex-fiancee's honeymoon place has returned from an 'amazing holiday' - but claims there was no romance.

John Whitbread, 32, - who became known as Jilted John - advertised on eBay after his girlfriend told him at Christmas she did not want to get married.

Desperate to find a holiday partner for the £1,950 trip to the Dominican Republic, John, from Donisthorpe, Leicestershire, tried to find a companion for the trip on eBay.

