Finally, after instead selling £10 raffle tickets - raising £1,410 for testicular cancer charity Balls To Cancer he jetted off to the Caribbean with lucky winner Kelly Wood - who he met for the first time at the airport.

John said he is constantly asked if they have become a couple. But he said this could not have been further from his mind.

He said : 'Everyone is hoping I've found romance again. Obviously not. I only recently split up with my girlfriend.'

He added: 'I have made a friend out of it and it's brilliant. It could have easily gone the other way.

'To go on holiday with a complete stranger and get on is incredible.

